sketch-2.bodyMarkdown:
A child can override a method and still build on the parent implementation.

```python
class Vehicle:
    def description(self):
        return self.make

class ElectricCar(Vehicle):
    def description(self):
        base = super().description()
        return f"{base} - electric"
```

This keeps shared behavior in one place while the child adds its own detail.

Before introducing a parent class, identify behavior that is truly identical across the child types. Inheritance should remove meaningful duplication while leaving each subclass’s special state and output visible.
